{
  "doc_id": "54901",
  "text": "A recent AASLD practice guideline on HCC has been published. [CITATION_1] Of the two tests prospectively evaluated as screening tools for HCC, alpha-fetoprotein (AFP) and ultrasound (US), the sensitivity, specificity, and diagnostic accuracy of US are higher than those of AFP. The AASLD Practice Guideline for HCC recommended surveillance of carriers at high risk of HCC with US every 6-12 months and AFP alone when US is not available or cost is an issue. [CITATION_2] Because the interpretation of US findings is operator dependent, clinicians may choose to employ both US and AFP for HCC surveillance. ",
